news.title: TNHB's two high-rise projects in Trichy will be completed as per schedule: Collector
news.para: The 464 dwelling units in the four high-rise towers -- each having 14-15 floors -- will be utilised under the Tamil Nadu Government Rental Housing Scheme (TNGRHS) to serve as residential quarters for the government employees.

news.title: China urges banks, insurers to support affordable rental housing
news.para: The China Banking and Insurance Regulatory Commission urged commercial banks to undertake affordable rental housing projects, according to a statement published on its website on Friday.

news.title: First-time home buyers in Jammu & Kashmir to get 50% stamp duty remission
news.para: The decision is aimed at giving a boost to the real-estate sector in Jammu and Kashmir and motivating the new buyers to participate in the market, he said.

news.title: Government 'soft' on illegal constructions in Ludhiana?
news.para: s the inquiry report submitted by additional commissioner Rishipal Singh has highlighted clear apathy of building branch officials, the MC Commissioner Pardeep Sabharwal has issued the show cause notices to over 100 employees, which many believe is a mere formality.

news.title: Telangana HC orders plots registrations with riders
news.para: While the case is now pending in Supreme Court after the state challenged it, the division bench order still stands as the SC did not stay it.

news.title: Nagpur civic body makes building plans, sanction charges must to construct in slums
news.para: NMC executive engineer and ‘competent authority (slum)’ Avinash Barhate issued a gazette notification on February 18 making it mandatory to get prior sanction of building plan from him for construction of houses in notified slum areas. As per state government norms, such notification needs to be issued every two years.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board e-auction finds five takers for 143 properties
news.para: An MIG (middle income group) flat in Sector 51 was sold for Rs 96.01 lakh against a reserve price of Rs 90 lakh; and another MIG flat in Sector 51 was sold for Rs 92.25 lakh against a reserve price of Rs 90 lakh.

news.title: Mumbai: Chembur Siddharth colony told to clear power dues post-2019
news.para: The issue was taken up by Shiv Sena MP Rahul Shewale on Friday at a meeting in Mantralaya where bureaucrats, representatives from Adani Electricity and colony residents were present.

news.title: Government has taken lot of steps to clean realty sector: Housing secretary
news.para: Manoj Joshi said the stamp duty in property transactions has come down and it should further reduce as this plays an important role in determining whether businesses are done in a fair manner or using black money.

news.title: Gurugram administration reconstitutes probe panel on Chintel Paradiso tower
news.para: It will have as members the chief engineer (building), PWD B&R; superintending engineer, Gurugram circle (PWD B&R); district town planner, enforcement; and Rajecv Kumar, ACP Udyog Vihar.

news.title: Telangana government to auction over 2,000 flats to realtors
news.para: The Hyderabad Metropolitan Development Authority (HMDA) will conduct auctions on March 24 and is hoping to get about Rs 1,000 crore.

news.title: Panel to resettle 100 more Chintels Paradiso families, has three months to file report
news.para: The families are apprehensive about the structural safety of their buildings and want to move out. They will be shifted to other flats within the society by the developer, officials said.

news.title: ATS Tourmaline residents concerned over water leakage in basement for eight months
news.para: Spread across 10 acres, the project was launched in 2013. Possession of flats started in 2019. Out of 410 flats, around 75 families are currently living in the five towers of the residential complex.

news.title: Haryana forms panel to examine structural strength of buildings
news.para: Kaushal made the statement days after the sequential collapse of drawing-room roofs of a flat from the sixth floor to the first floor in a highrise in the city, in which two women residents of the building were killed and a senior central government officer was critically injured.

news.title: Two more China Evergrande property assets taken over by state-owned firms
news.para: The world's most indebted property developer on Jan. 26 transferred its control over a theme park called Evergrande Fairyland in the Nansha district of Guangzhou to Minmetals International Trust Co, according to the records.
